32 SUMMARY
3333 This bill, based on the recommendations of the Blue Ribbon Commission to Study
3344 Emergency Medical Services in the State, reduces the number of members appointed to the
3355 Emergency Medical Services' Board, other than the members representing regional
3366 councils, from 12 to 5, provides for regular feedback and recommendations from each
3377 region and requires the board to report annually by January 1st to the joint standing
3388 committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over emergency medical services matters
3399 any recommended changes to the Maine Emergency Medical Services Act of 1982 or other
4400 necessary changes to improve the provision of emergency medical services and allows the
4411 committee to report out legislation based on the board's recommendations.
